item.title: DSA - Linked List
item.description: What is a Linked List? A linked list is a common data structure that is similar to an array, but its order is based on pointers to the next element in memory instead of using physical placement (indices). A linked list has two main components: ListNode class: This class has a val property that represents the value and a next property that represents a pointer to the next element in memory.
